South Korean Foreign Minister Han Sung-Joo has  begun a brief visit to Thailand for talks stressing bilateral and regional  relations, officials said Wednesday.
Han, who started a tour of four regional nations in the Philippines, is to  visit Vietnam and Indonesia after Thailand.
He was scheduled to meet his Thai counterpart, Prasong Soonsiri, later in  the day after a courtesy call on Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai and an audience  with King Bhumibol Adulyadej.
Han is scheduled to leave Bangkok on Thursday.
